Spells per Day	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.NavigatorWizardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A navigator-wizard continues training in magic as well as his own field of research. Thus, when a new navigator-wizard level is gained, the character also gains spells as if he had also gained a level in a spellcasting class he belonged to before he added the prestige class. He does not, however, get any additional benefits a charachter of that class would have gained, only the new spells. This essentially means that he adds the level of navigator-wizard to the level of another spellcasting class the character already has and then determines spells per day and caster level accordingly. If the caster had more than one spellcasting class before he became a navigator-wizard, he must decide to which class he adds each level of navigator-wizard for the purposes of determining spells per dat when he add the new level.	KEY:Navigator-Wizard ~ Spells per Day																										SORTKEY:Class_Navigator_Wizard	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Infallible Direction	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.NavigatorWizardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A navigator-wizard automatically knows where the north lies. This grant a +2 competence bonis to all Navigation checks.	KEY:Navigator-Wizard ~ Infallible Direction																										SORTKEY:Class_Navigator_Wizard	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Fast Pursuit	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.NavigatorWizardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The 2nd level navigator-wizard learns to manoeuvre his ship to take best advantage of wind and wave to gain an advantage over any other vessel he is pursuing or trying to escape from. He may add his class level to any opposed Seamanship checks made when invleved in a pursuit.	KEY:Navigator-Wizard ~ Fast Pursuit																										SORTKEY:Class_Navigator_Wizard	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Intuitive Seamanship	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.NavigatorWizardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 3rd level, a navigator-wizard learns how to get the very best out of his ship and his creq. All Seamanship checks made by the navigator-wizard or his crew receive a +2 competence bonus. At 6th and 9th level this bonus rises to +4 and +6 respectively.	KEY:Navigator-Wizard ~ Intuitive Seamanship				DEFINE:IntuitiveSeamanshipBonus|0					BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Seamanship)|IntuitiveSeamanshipBonus|TYPE=Competence	BONUS:VAR|IntuitiveSeamanshipBonus|((NavigatorWizardLVL/3)*2)																SORTKEY:Class_Navigator_Wizard	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
Catch the Wind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.NavigatorWizardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:On achieving 4th level, the navigator-wizard is able to manoeuvre his ship to take best advantage of winds and currents for sustained periods of time and may freely cast minor incantations to influence them. Any ship with a navigator-wizard on board may increase both its base and daily movement rate by 10%%.	KEY:Navigator-Wizard ~ Catch the Wind																										SORTKEY:Class_Navigator_Wizard	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
True Voyage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.NavigatorWizardClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 5th level the navigator wizard will never become lost at sea. He automatically passes al future Navigation checks, unless thrown off course by magical means (such as teleportation).	KEY:Navigator-Wizard ~ True Voyage																										SORTKEY:Class_Navigator_Wizard	SOURCEPAGE:SoB
